    <refsection id="Description_MEAB_OpAmp">
        <title>Description</title>
        <para>
            This block is a simple nonideal model of an OpAmp with a Vout =f(Vin) characteristic 
            (with Vin the difference between positive and negative pin of the input port) which is limited by VMin and VMax.
            The slope at Vin=0 must be positive (or the absolute slope is taken into account in the calculations).
            The output Vout is computed in this way:
        </para>
        <para>
            <latex>
                \begin{eqnarray}
                \Large{Vout} = \frac {\Large{VMax+VMin}}{2} + \frac{\Large{Slope*Vin}}{\Large{1+Slope*|\frac{2}{VMax-VMin}*Vin|}}
                \end{eqnarray}
            </latex>
        </para>
    </refsection>
